2025-09-10T09:21:39.3105007Z [32m[4;32mWould you like to see a more detailed list of what I will do?
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3105692Z [0mNo TTY, assuming you would say yes :)
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3109706Z
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3109927Z I will:
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3110161Z
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3110415Z  - make sure your computer doesn't already have Nix files
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3111217Z    (if it does, I will tell you how to clean them up.)
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3111840Z  - create local users (see the list above for the users I'll make)
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3112392Z  - create a local group (nixbld)
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3112657Z  - install Nix in /nix
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3112889Z  - create a configuration file in /etc/nix
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3113217Z  - set up the "default profile" by creating some Nix-related files in
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3113523Z    /root
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3126952Z  - back up /etc/bash.bashrc to /etc/bash.bashrc.backup-before-nix
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3127646Z  - update /etc/bash.bashrc to include some Nix configuration
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3138684Z  - load and start a service (at /etc/systemd/system/nix-daemon.service
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3139410Z    and /etc/systemd/system/nix-daemon.socket) for nix-daemon
