2025-09-10T09:21:39.3173867Z [34m---- let's talk about sudo -----------------------------------------------------
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3184015Z [0mThis script is going to call sudo a lot. Normally, it would show you
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3184734Z exactly what commands it is running and why. However, the script is
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3185227Z run in a headless fashion, like this:
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3185390Z
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3185527Z   $ curl -L https://nixos.org/nix/install | sh
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3185857Z
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3186116Z or maybe in a CI pipeline. Because of that, I'm going to skip the
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3186538Z verbose output in the interest of brevity.
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3186712Z
2025-09-10T09:21:39.3186789Z If you would like to
